Super Eagles forward, Moses Simon, has described the Sudanese side as a strong team. Simon said the match against Sudan was more difficult than that of Egypt. The Super Eagles forward disclosed this while addressing the press after receiving the man of the match award. According to Simon: “The Sudanese side side was more difficult than the Egyptians, but we expected it. “They played a very good game and I’m happy. I’m not just the man of the match, but the man of the match award goes to the entire team.” Super Eagles defeated the Sudanese side 3-1 in their second leg encounter in the ongoing African Cup of Nations, AFCON, in Cameroon.